#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
	printf("Step A\nRTT_total = RTT_dns1 + RTT_dns2 + RTT_dns3 + RTT_http1(tcp) + RTT_http1(obj)\nRTT_total = 3ms + 20ms + 26ms + 47ms + 47ms = 143 ms\n\nStep B\nRTT_total = RTT_dns1 + RTT_dns2 + RTT_dns3 + RTT_http1(tcp) + RTT_http1(obj) + RTT_http2(tcp) + RTT_http2(obj) + RTT_http3(tcp) + RTT_http3(obj) + RTT_http4(tcp) + RTT_http4(obj) + RTT_http5(tcp) + RTT_http5(obj) + RTT_http6(tcp) + RTT_http6(obj)\nRTT_total = 3ms + 20ms + 26ms + 47ms * 12 = 613 ms\n\nStep C\nPersistent case:\nRTT_total = RTT_dns1 + RTT_dns2 + RTT_dns3 + MAX ( RTT_http1(tcp) + RTT_http1(obj), RTT_http2(tcp) + RTT_http2(obj), RTT_http3(tcp) + RTT_http3(obj), RTT_http4(tcp) + RTT_http4(obj), RTT_http5(tcp) + RTT_http5(obj), RTT_http6(tcp) + RTT_http6(obj) )\nRTT_total = 3ms + 20ms + 26ms + 47ms * 2 = 143 ms\nNon-persistent case:\nRTT_total = RTT_dns1 + RTT_dns2 + RTT_dns3 + MAX ( RTT_http1(tcp) + RTT_http1(obj), RTT_http2(tcp) + RTT_http2(obj), RTT_http3(tcp) + RTT_http3(obj), RTT_http4(tcp) + RTT_http4(obj), RTT_http5(tcp) + RTT_http5(obj), RTT_http6(tcp) + RTT_http6(obj) )\nRTT_total = 3ms + 20ms + 26ms + 47ms * 2 = 143 ms\nSince parallel TCP connections allow for concurrent object transfer, persistence does not affect RTT. If parallel TCP connections were not allowed, persistence would reduce RTT by a figure that approaches 50 percent as the number of objects persistently transferred reaches infinity.\n");
}
